  "site_name": "135 DRUMMOND ROAD",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed change of use by reason of the housing typology of the existing building would fail to comply with the criteria set out in policies DC4 and DC5 of the Havering Core Strategy Development Control Policies and Development Control Document DPD 2008. As this is an inherent issue with the application site, and the explicit wording in policies DC4 and DC5, no conditions or obligations are able to overcome these policy issues, and the proposed development would therefore be unacceptable.",
    "The proposal, by reason of the increased amounts of activity within the building and outdoor areas, together with an intensification of the residential use in such close proximity to the neighbouring property, would result in unacceptable levels of noise and disturbance and comings and goings to the detriment of residential amenity of nearby residents.  The development would create an uplift in occupancy which would be out of keeping with the surrounding suburban context, which would be over and above what could be regarded as acceptable and reasonably expected with a single family house and would be detrimental to local character and the amenity of adjoining and nearby occupiers.The proposal is therefore contrary to Policy DC4 and DC61 of the Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The proposed development would, by reason of the inadequate provision of adequate communal area as well as lack provision for refuse and recycle storage, result in a cramped and poor living environment to the detriment of future occupiers the site. In this regards the proposal would be contrary to policy DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD and the advice given in National Planning Policy Framework, which requires the provision of high quality dwellings.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to the agent prior to the issue of any decision on the application."
  ],
